      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "Spokane labor was honored at\nthe meeting of the State Federation\nof Labor which closed its labors\nat Aberdeen, Wash. last Satur-\nday. Mr.. A. w. Jones who repre-\nsented the local cigarmaker's un-\nion was elected End vice-president\nof the Federation by unanimous\nvvote.\n\n\nThe election OF Mr.. Jones gives\ngreat satisfaction to local union\nmen, Mr.. Jones being one OF the\nmost able and conservative leaders\nof labor in eastern Washington. G.\nr. Case. carpenter OF Everett,\nwas elected president and G. o.\nYoung who Is we'll known In Spo-\nkane, was reelected organizer for\nthe American Federation of Labor.\nThe next meeting will be held In\nBellingham."
    }
  ]
